HEADWORD: Profitable
<hw>Prof"it*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>profitable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Yielding or bringing profit or gain;
gainful; lucrative; useful; helpful; advantageous; beneficial; <as>as, a
<ex>profitable</ex> trade; <ex>profitable</ex> business; a
<ex>profitable</ex> study or profession.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What was so <qex>profitable</qex> to the empire became fatal to
the⟦br⟧
emperor.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Prof"it*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Prof"it*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
